  "distance": "214.200 miles (344.700 km)",
  "event_preview": "Barber Motorsports Park is a 2.38-mile (3.83 km) permanent road course in Birmingham, Alabama, featuring 17 turns and 80 feet of elevation change. Built by George W. Barber and opened in 2003, it has been referred to as the Augusta National of Motorsports for its immaculate landscaping and sculpture-lined infield. The Children's of Alabama Indy Grand Prix is the fourth race of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season and the 16th running of the event at this venue, contested over 90 laps. Josef Newgarden holds the all-time wins record at Barber with three victories. The all-time qualifying lap record belongs to Pato O'Ward, who turned a 1:05.847 in 2021 after the circuit was resurfaced, shattering the previous mark by nearly nine tenths of a second. The fastest lap in race conditions — 1:06.8182, also set by O'Ward in 2021 — remains the benchmark for race pace at the Alabama circuit.",
